"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-culture-culture-news-prosecutors-investigating-harassment-olympics-artistic-director-1235073166\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByJon Blistein  Prosecutors in Paris are investigating death threats and harassment directed at Thomas Jolly, the artistic director behind theopening ceremony at the 2024 Olympics, according toThe Associated Press.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31, \"end\": 36, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 96, \"end\": 102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9880673861374819, \"rank\": 0.01175534942756667, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.8255339122151121, \"rank\": 0.21133727543255904, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The investigation was launched, the Paris prosecutor's office said, after Jolly filed a police complaint on Tuesday, July 30 (the opening ceremony took place a few days prior, on July 26).\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly said he'd been subjected to death threats, \\\"public insults,\\\" and \\\"defamation\\\" and has been \\\"the target of threatening messages and insults on social networks criticizing his sexual orientation and his wrongly-assumed Israeli roots.\\\"\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 628, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9808479948147066, \"rank\": 0.01908917888269541, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly's opening ceremony was one of the wildest and most memorable in recent Olympic history.\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It featuredC\\u00e9line Dion's grand returnto the stage,Lady Gaga honoringFrench cabaret icon Zizi Jeanmaire, and French metal greats Gojira performing the revolutionary anthem, \\\"Ah!\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9748423321923971, \"rank\": 0.02401027515697016, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.459571971612755e-27, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c7a Ira\\\" alongside a beheaded and bloodied Marie Antoinette.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.36894221907679e-30, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Jolly's intention to deliver a maximalist display that leaned into French clich\\u00e9s and stereotypes.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9748423321923971, \"rank\": 0.02401027515697016, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a previousinterview withThe AP, he said, \\\"When we watchEmily in ParisorAm\\u00e9lie Poulain, we know it's not quite the real Paris.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.899220424458661e-15, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are going to play with all those cliches, but we are also going to challenge them.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is also a vibrant youth.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Different cultures rubbing shoulders in the streets.\\\"\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, unsurprisingly, not everyone appreciated the spectacle, especially those on the right.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, controversial men's rights figure Andrew Tatetried to claimthe beheaded Marie Antoinette scene was Satanic, a suggestion Gojira's Joe Duplantierdismissed outright toRolling Stone: \\\"It's none of that.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1611, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.459571971612755e-27, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 1620, \"end\": 1623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.5343762425765961, \"rank\": 0.7689440339777406, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's French history.\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's French charm, you know, beheaded people, red wine, and blood all over the place - it's romantic, it's normal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9748423321923971, \"rank\": 0.02401027515697016, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was additional uproar over a scene featuring drag queens and dancers at a long table that some argued was a reference to Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" and, thus, insulting to Christians.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0308356796426338e-22, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.759050967095291, \"rank\": 0.31687243038272134, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Donald Trump evenchimed inon this one, calling the scene a \\\"disgrace\\\" and saying if he was elected president again, there'd be no such mockery of \\\"The Last Supper\\\" at the 2028 games in Los Angeles.Editor's picksThe 250 Greatest Albums of the 21st Century So FarThe 100 Best TV Episodes of All TimeThe 500 Greatest Albums of All Time100 Best Movies of the 21st Century  Jolly, however,denied being inspiredby the painting.\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 1.7846441548648475e-11, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, he said the scene was meant to pay homage to Greek mythology and the origins of theOlympicsin ancient Greece.\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2505, \"end\": 2520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999878700376844, \"rank\": 1.2130109532432963e-05, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9998715471536537, \"rank\": 0.0001254600761334603, \"text\": \"ancient Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly has received plenty of support from Olympic officials and local politicians.\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the opening ceremony, aParis 2024 spokespersonsaid, \\\"Clearly, there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, I think that Thomas Jolly really tried to celebrate community tolerance.\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9880673861374819, \"rank\": 0.01175534942756667, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are really sorry.\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Trending StoriesJohn Lithgow Knows J.K. Rowling's Anti-Trans Views Will Now Forever Come Up in 'Every Interview'Kevin Spacey's 'Mental Illness' Should Trigger $29.5 Million Payout, 'House of Cards' Trial Jurors HearBTS Nails Its Comeback With 'Arirang'Top Disaster Response Official Claims He Teleported to a Waffle House  Anne Hidalgo, mayor of Paris, also backed Jolly following the news of the investigation into the online harassment against him.\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 3437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3296, \"end\": 3308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waffle_House\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Waffle House\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waffle_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Waffle_House\"}, {\"begin\": 3310, \"end\": 3322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 3333, \"end\": 3338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Jolly held our values high,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a pride and an honor for Paris to be able to count on his talent to magnify our city and tell the world who we are.\\\"\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3511, \"end\": 3516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8344717717752378e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly is actually the second person to file a police complaint over alleged online harassment related to the opening ceremony after Barbara Butch - a popular DJ and LGBTQ activist who performed during the misinterpreted \\\"Last Supper\\\" scene -brought one earlier this week.\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We want to hear it.\", \"from\": 3877, \"to\": 3896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Send us a tip using our anonymous form.\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rolling Stone is a part of Penske Media Corporation.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3938, \"end\": 3951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.668956334460561e-23, \"text\": \"Rolling Stone\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rolling_Stone\"}, {\"begin\": 3965, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penske Media\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penske_Media_Corporation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Rolling Stone, LLC.\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4013, \"end\": 4016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999989370027117, \"rank\": 1.0629982829865062e-06, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\":